title: Lyft IPO will encourage other companies to go public, says former NASDAQ CEO
text: Robert Greifeld, former NASDAQ CEO, discusses Lyft's upcoming IPO with CNBC's "Closing Bell."

title: What The Experts Are Saying Ahead Of Lyft's IPO
text: Ride-hailing company Lyft will see its shares trade on a public market for the first time Friday. Ahead of the much-anticipated IPO, the following is a roundup of what industry experts are saying.

title: On eve of Lyft's much-hyped debut, Warren Buffett says regular investors shouldn't buy hot IPOs
text: Amid a glut of IPOs this year, Berkshire Hathaway's CEO warns retail investors not to get carried away with the euphoria.

title: Buffett: Average investors shouldn't buy 'hot' IPOs
text: Berkshire Hathaway's Warren Buffett sits down with CNBC's Becky Quick in Grapevine Texas at an event for Hand-up Success. They discuss the state of the economy, his investment strategy and Lyft's inital public offering.

title: Sophia the robotic social media star
text: CNBC's Karen Tso catches up with 3-year-old humanoid robot, Sophia, who has 96.2 thousand followers on Twitter and 98 thousand followers on Instagram.

title: Lyft wants to catch up, get ahead of Uber, says former Trulia CEO
text: Former Trulia CEO Peter Flint joins "Squawk Alley" to discuss Lyft's upcoming IPO and how it can compete with Uber, which is also expected to IPO in 2019.

title: Jim Cramer's on Lyft's IPO
text: Jim Cramer & Katherine Ross on the floor of the NYSE.

title: Lyft investor's bull case for IPO market
text: David Chao, co-founder and general partner of DCM and Lyft investor, and CNBC's Pisani discuss Lyft's impending IPO and the company's profitability on "Squawk Alley."

title: Huawei equipment raises red flags in the UK
text: Aikiko Fujita reports on the report released by the U.K. government expressing concerns over Huawei software.

title: U.S. 4Q GDP Grew at 2.2% Pace, Revised Down From 2.6%
text: Megan Greene, chief economist at Manulife Asset Management, and Thomas Digenan, head of U.S. intrinsic value equity at UBS Asset Management, examine fourth-quarter U.S. economic growth. They speak on "Bloomberg Daybreak: Americas."

title: Here's what investors should expect from a Lyft IPO
text: Jim McVeigh, CEO of Cyndx, joins "Squawk Box" to discuss what investors can expect from Lyft's IPO.

title: Is Lyft Worth $19 Billion?
text: Lyft has very strong revenue growth but lost almost $1 billion last year. However, when you compare its Enterprise Value to revenue valuation metric vs. various public companies it going public at $68 (or a bit above that) isn’t unreasonable.

title: The Wall Street Journal: Equipment from China’s Huawei has major security flaws, U.K. says
text: British officials accused Huawei Technologies Co. of repeatedly failing to address security flaws in its products and said the company hasn’t demonstrated a commitment to fixing them.

title: Howard Gold's No-Nonsense Investing: These investors are the big winners from Lyft and other unicorn IPOs
text: VCs, Wall Street are rushing to cash out of the hottest private companies while the getting is good, writes Howard Gold.

title: Lyft and Uber's European rivals are trying to make money before going public
text: European ride-hailing and carpooling start-ups are more focused on profitability than their U.S. counterparts.
